virtual void SystemsBiologyWorkbench::sbwSignatureType::read (  DataBlockReader    reader,
va_list &    ap
)  [pure virtual]
 

For C API : read a value from a given data block.

The type of the value is assumed to correspond to this sbwSignatureType.

Parameters:
reader  data block in which the value is stored.
ap  variable argument list - the next item is assumed to be a pointer, the extracted value is stored in the referenced location.

Implemented in SystemsBiologyWorkbench::sbwSignatureByte.

virtual void SystemsBiologyWorkbench::sbwSignatureType::read1DArray (  DataBlockReader    reader,
Integer &    size,
va_list &    ap
)  [pure virtual]
 

For C API : read an array from a data block.

The type of the elements is assumed to correspond to this sbwSignatureType.

Parameters:
reader  data block in which array is stored
size  number of elements in the array
ap  variable argument list - the next item is assumed to be a pointer to a pointer to an array. This pointer is changed to point to an array allocated on the C Heap. Use SBWFree to deallocate this array. (unless its a string array in which case use SBWFree2DArray)

Implemented in SystemsBiologyWorkbench::sbwSignatureByte.

Integer &    xsize,
Integer &    ysize,
va_list &   
)  [pure virtual]
 

For C API : read a 2D array from a data block.

Parameters:
reader  data block in which array is stored
xSize  set to the number of elements on the first dimension of the array
ySize  set to the number of elements on the first dimension of the array
ap  variable argument list - the next item is assumed to be a pointer to a pointer to a pointer array. This pointer is changed to point to a pointer array allocated on the C Heap. Use SBWFree2DArray to deallocate this array. (doesn't work for string 2D string arrays)

Implemented in SystemsBiologyWorkbench::sbwSignatureByte.
